<h1>AFTER</h1>
Thanks everyone for coming.  Sorry about the debugging at the end.  In the end the problem was that the SimpleOpenNI Libray returns zero for the shadows so I had to change the if statement to " if (thisDepth != 0 &amp;&amp; thisDepth &lt; threshold)" and use large threshold numbers like between 500 and 5000.  Below is the code we were working on in the session which now works.  Also because at the end I retreated to <a href="http://www.shiffman.net/p5/kinect/">Shiffman's library</a> (easier but does not do skeleton or work on a pc) here is those <a href="http://itp.nyu.edu/varwiki/Classword/HRS10code#KinectAverageOfCloseSpots">examples</a> (remember to either comment out the "public class blabla extends PApplet" line or rename your sketch "blabla").

<pre>
<code>
import SimpleOpenNI.*;

SimpleOpenNI  camera;
int threshold = 850;

void setup() {
  camera = new SimpleOpenNI(this);
  camera.enableDepth();
  size(camera.depthWidth(), camera.depthHeight());
}

void draw() {
  camera.update();
  int allNearXPosAddedUp =  0;
  int allNearYPosAddedUp  = 0;
  int allPos = 0;

  int[] depthArray = camera.depthMap();
  for ( int row = 0; row < camera.depthHeight(); row++) {
    for ( int col = 0; col < camera.depthWidth(); col++) {
      int offsetInBigArray = row*camera.depthWidth() + col;
      int thisDepth = depthArray[ offsetInBigArray ];
      if (thisDepth != 0 && thisDepth < threshold) { //the shadows turn out to be 0
        allNearXPosAddedUp =  allNearXPosAddedUp  + col;
        allNearYPosAddedUp  = allNearYPosAddedUp  + row;
        allPos++;
        camera.depthImage().pixels[offsetInBigArray] = color(255, 0, 0);
      }
    }
  }
  image(camera.depthImage(), 0, 0);
  if (allPos != 0) {
    int averageXPos = allNearXPosAddedUp/allPos;
    int averageYPos = allNearYPosAddedUp/allPos;
    ellipse(averageXPos, averageYPos, 30, 30);
  }
}

void keyPressed() {
  if (key == '-') {
    threshold--;
  } 
  else if (key == '=') {
    threshold++;
  }
  println("Threshold " + threshold);
}

</code>
</pre>

