Anyone wanna learn vim?

&nbsp;
<div>For those who don't know, vim is one of the most powerful text editors around...a program that can be run entirely from terminal that can be used to write code, markup or even a novel.  In it's almost 40 year history, vim has been sharpened into one of the most powerful and fastest tools in our cultural arsenal for writing and manipulating text.  Most people who use / are aware of it are from technical backgrounds, but once I picked it up, I've used it for all sorts of writing and journaling.</div>
&nbsp;
<div>vim has a notoriously steep learning curve, but as an experienced vim user and a decent explainer, I think I could help demystify it.  I'd be happy to put on an hour or even 30 minute long vim session to show off some of the powerful features of this program, and help everyone write faster, feel geekier and ditch microsoft office for an incredible piece of free software!</div>

