A hands-on workshop to guide you through techniques, gears and tips to film in environments requiring a high degree of mobility:

- Story telling from mountain tops to urban jungles;
- Capturing concerts/performances in a more dynamic way;
- Shooting from moving vehicles: car, bike, board, and many more;
- Managing weather:  snow, rain, water, sand, dust, etc;
- Chasing or running away from wild life, natural disasters and/or hysteric fans;
- etc

In all cases, you often have to work fast, haul all your stuff w/ you, remain mobile (for a quick exit, if needed) and avoid destroying your equipment.

We will also cover tips about airline travel with filming equipment / insurance / battery management (options to recharge are not always available) / lens selection / portable lighting / audio / editing on the go / footage backup strategy / how to tone down your expensive cameras -- especially if you are in poor and remote corners of the world.

I will bring all sorts of equipment you can test out:  steadycam, ultra light tripods, GoPro Camera, flying drone, under-water casing, lights,  portable rigs, travel cases, reflectors, wireless mics, etc.  I will also show footage to illustrate what the gear does for you.

